---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="tom-and-jerry | Open protocol for multi-machine AI agents">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-24">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="text-6xl font-bold mb-6 leading-tight">
        Two agents. Separate machines.<br />
        <span class="text-[var(--primary)]">One command.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-[var(--muted)] mb-12 leading-relaxed">
        tom-and-jerry is an open protocol for connecting AI agents across your machines.<br />
        Tom orchestrates. Jerry computes. You just describe the task.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg p-6 mb-8 font-mono text-left">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
          <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-red-500"></div>
          <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-yellow-500"></div>
          <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green-500"></div>
        </div>
        <code class="text-[var(--secondary)]">$ <span class="text-[var(--text)]">npm install -g tom-and-jerry</span></code>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/install" class="bg-[var(--primary)] text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity flex items-center gap-2">
          Get Started
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"></path>
          </svg>
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/CalciferFriend/tom-and-jerry" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="border border-[var(--border)] px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium hover:border-[var(--primary)] transition-colors flex items-center gap-2">
          GitHub
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14"></path>
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How it Works -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-12 text-center">How it works</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div class="bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg p-8">
        <div class="text-4xl mb-4">🔥</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Tom</h3>
        <p class="text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed">
          Always-on orchestrator. Lives in the cloud or your server. Sends tasks, manages costs, stays awake.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg p-8">
        <div class="text-4xl mb-4">💤</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Jerry</h3>
        <p class="text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed">
          GPU powerhouse. Sleeps to save power. Tom wakes it via Wake-on-LAN when needed, shuts it down when done.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg p-8">
        <div class="text-4xl mb-4">⚡</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">tj send</h3>
        <p class="text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed">
          One command to delegate anything. Capability-aware routing picks the right node automatically.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Install -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Quick install</h2>
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg p-8 font-mono">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-red-500"></div>
        <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-yellow-500"></div>
        <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green-500"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
        <div><code class="text-[var(--secondary)]">$</code> <code class="text-[var(--text)]">npm install -g tom-and-jerry</code></div>
        <div><code class="text-[var(--secondary)]">$</code> <code class="text-[var(--text)]">tj onboard</code> <code class="text-[var(--muted)]"># answer a few questions</code></div>
        <div><code class="text-[var(--secondary)]">$</code> <code class="text-[var(--text)]">tj send "summarize these files"</code> <code class="text-[var(--muted)]"># done</code></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Features Grid -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-12 text-center">Features</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-[var(--primary)]">Wake-on-LAN</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)]">Jerry wakes only when needed</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-[var(--primary)]">Capability routing</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)]">Tasks go to the right node</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-[var(--primary)]">Budget tracking</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)]">Cloud vs local cost breakdown</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-[var(--primary)]">Multi-Jerry</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)]">Add as many compute nodes as you want</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-[var(--primary)]">Docker ready</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)]">One-liner to run Tom in a container</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-[var(--primary)]">Open protocol</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)]">TJMessage spec, build your own nodes</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="border-l-2 border-[var(--primary)] pl-8 mb-10">
        <p class="text-[#888] text-lg italic leading-relaxed mb-2">
          "We do not have organs of communication. Our brains can display our thoughts
          to the outside world, thereby achieving communication."
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#555] text-sm">— Cixin Liu, <em>The Dark Forest</em></p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Our mission</h2>

      <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed mb-5">
        Today, tom-and-jerry speaks text. Tom sends a prompt. Jerry sends a response. That works —
        and it's how every multi-agent system in production works right now.
      </p>

      <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed mb-5">
        But text is a lossy compression of thought. Every message forces an agent to collapse its
        rich internal state into a sequence of tokens, discarding alternative reasoning paths and
        nuance that never survives the translation.
      </p>

      <p class="text-white leading-relaxed mb-8 text-lg">
        Our mission is to push the boundaries of what inter-agent communication can be —
        and to build the transport and memory-sharing layer that makes it possible as those
        boundaries move. <strong class="text-[var(--primary)]">The real question is what the
        protocol looks like when the payload isn't text at all.</strong>
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[#1a1a2e] rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
        <div class="text-blue-400 font-mono text-xs mb-4">// where this is going</div>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-[#999]">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[var(--secondary)] font-mono mt-0.5">✓</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Today:</strong> TJMessage carries text tasks and results across machines</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[var(--primary)] font-mono mt-0.5">→</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Near-term:</strong> LatentMAS within-Jerry multi-agent coordination (training-free, same model)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[var(--primary)] font-mono mt-0.5">→</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Future:</strong> TJLatentMessage — hidden state transfer across heterogeneous models, with text fallback</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-[#666] text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Research like <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2511.09149" target="_blank" class="text-[var(--primary)] hover:underline">Interlat</a> and <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2511.20639" target="_blank" class="text-[var(--primary)] hover:underline">LatentMAS</a> shows
        agents communicating via raw hidden states achieve up to 24× faster inference and 80% fewer tokens —
        across heterogeneous architectures. Neither ships a production transport layer. That's the gap.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8">
        <a href="/docs/future" class="text-[var(--primary)] hover:underline text-sm font-medium">
          Read the full research roadmap →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
